If you should ever find yourself traveling the Alaskan highway system through the eastern part of state you’re sure to be amazed by a multitude of natural wonders but some of the more stunning and scenic views are of Mt Drum — perhaps the most photogenic mountain in all of Alaska. Located several miles east of Glennallen, and nestled neatly within the confines of the Wrangell St. Elias national park, Mt. Drum towers over the nearby villages and dominates the landscape. As you approach from the east you first begin to notice its magnitude at a scenic turnoff near mile marker 176 on the Glenn Highway; right at the welcome to Tolsona sign. This is the spot where many well known social media pictures have been taken and a placard marks the spot and provides a lot of rich information about its history. From the north she is often overshadowed by her much larger neighbor Mt. Sanford with some of the more notable photo opportunities to photograph them together coming along the Tok Cutoff Highway. The closest you can get on the road system is a small dirt road located just to the north of the Gulkana Airport. Here are just a few of the many photos I have taken of Mt. Drum over the years. Mt. Drum, along with the other Wrangell Mountains, are a big part of our daily lives here in the Copper River Valley. Every time you step outside your car they’re the biggest thing you see. Should you choose to photograph Drum or the others for yourself I recommend you do so either just before dusk, when they’re  drenched in alpenglow, or at night when you can see the Milky Way or the Aurora right over the tops. — Copper River Valley, Alaska.

"Far Western Nepal"
Also called sometimes"the Doti Region"
It's massive! The nature here is unexplored to a great extent for the fact being it's far from the capital.
I don't know where to start and where to end, for it includes so much more than you find in these pictures,so it's up to you to explore the rest!
Some of the fascinating sites includes:
Alpine meadows, forest and lakes
Khaptad National Park, this is a must!
Mount Api (7132m), highest in the region
Suklaphanta National Park (popular for the Swamp Deer)
Bardia National Park
Mt. Saipal
#canoeing
Jungle #safari
Karnali River ( Platanista #dolphin are found)
#trekking ,#hiking #rafting ,
And on and on!
I can't include all places too cause the list is even longer, so explore through media and by yourself!

I wake up at 4am every morning, and despite it occurring every single day, I marvel at the sun each time i catch it at sunrise.  It's one of the only times I realize we are all on a planet spinning around a ball of hot gas. ...in a solar system ...in a whole universe.  And for me..each morning I get to see sunrise, I'm reminded  that the things that I sometimes herald as major problems/concerns are really almost trivial in the grand scheme of life,  and everything else going on in the world, and beyond. ...every morning I do my best to forgive yesterday's mistakes, and trespasses...to reset and appreciate just being alive. ☀️Sunrise is my daily reminder to appreciate every minute I have, and the people I care about. Because tomorrow isnt promised. (Swipe ⬅️🌅) #livefree #youwontmakeitoutalive #dowhatmakesyoufeelgood

Good old times? No, that's just your nostalgic interpretation of what happened, we live now and that's it. 
This sunset is actually from the end of our last year's climbing hike to Wildspitze, one of the highest mountains in Austria, we set off at
2am and then we took quite a long drive from Czech republic to Vent, Austria where we started to hike at 7am, it took us 11 hours full of magnificent lookouts and that's the best thing about Alps, the higher you get the more beautiful it is. This picture is taken at the Breslauer Hütte, we could call it our "Basecamp" since it's right about in the first third of the hike and most of the people sleep here overnight, we built up our tent and went to sleep without any regrets. 🏕️🏞️🏔️

Chemistry is committed to craft cannabis. We work almost exclusively with smaller family run and legacy farms, all of which practice organic farming techniques to grow some of the finest sun grown weed in Northern California.

Last year our founder and CEO Paul Roethle (left) met with Alpenglow Farm’s Craig Johnson (right) to tour the Southern Humboldt farm he runs alongside his wife, Melanie. Alpenglow’s lovingly cultivated cannabis has been hand-selected to create a number of Chemistry’s full-spectrum products, including our popular Trident tincture and the knockout Blood Orange Kush vape that will be released VERY soon.

@Alpenglowfarms707 actually goes above and beyond organic by enacting DEM Pure certified farming practices to create a richly diverse biome with polyculture and living soil.

Throwback Thursday! Dorothy looks over the crowd at the original Emerald City amphitheater in June of 1970. .
.
During the Magic Moment Show, she would disappear onstage in a puff of smoke after she clicked her heels, and then instantly reappear overhead in one of the balloons from the Balloon Ride. While a simple trick of using an actress double in an identical costume, the result was extremely effective. .
.
While the Emerald City no longer exists at Land of Oz, Autumn at Oz has recently begun creating an Emerald City area, which now includes a finale show for the first time since 1980! .
.
Tickets on sale now for “Journey with Dorothy” our interactive tour down the Yellow Brick Road where your family and friends get the chance to play the Scarecrow, Tinman, Lion, Glinda, or the Witch alongside Dorothy! .
.
Tickets are $27.50 (+taxes & fees) for selective days in June & July 5th.  Available at www.landofoznc.com .
.
Want to meet all the characters? Check out information on our “Autumn at Oz” Festival coming this September. Celebrate the 80th anniversary of The Wizard of Oz during the largest Oz Event in the world! .

Today is my final day of instructing @bigskyresort for the 2018/19 season, and I’m already counting down the days until opening day next year. I’ve spent my last week skiing with some of my favorite little local rippers. On their kindergarten and Pre-school spring break, they have made black tree runs look casual, continually begged for “just one more” April powder lap in the bowl, and giggled endlessly. These girls have taken on challenges fearlessly throughout the season and it’s been amazing to watch their skiing progress over the winter. They are tough as nails when they crash, always excited for another run, and a perfect example of why spending time in the mountains is so important. I honestly cannot wait to have them leaving me in the dust on Headwaters hikes and tram laps in the near future! .
.
.

The Ridge at Burke Mountain is a premium collection of new 3, 4 and 5 bedroom single family homes located on Burke Mountain in family-friendly Coquitlam, BC. These mountain-side detached homes offer over 3,200 to 3,800+ sq.ft. of luxurious living space, attached two car garages, over-height ceilings (double height great rooms in certain home plans) and expansive windows allowing for plenty of natural light, large entertainment-size kitchens complete with high-end Bosch stainless steel appliances, and top-of-the-line ‘Platinum Collection’ finishes throughout. Homes boast generous outdoor living space including welcoming front verandas, balconies and patios allowing you to take in the views of Mount Baker and the Fraser Valley below. Many homes also feature full above ground basements. ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Each new home can be personalized in our on-site Foxridge Design Centre where homeowners choose from hundreds of colours, materials, finishes and optional upgrades including finishing the basement level.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
The Ridge at Burke Mountain offers doorstep access to dozens of family-friendly parks and playgrounds (and more on the way), extensive hiking trails, streams, and Pinecone Burke Provincial Park; newer facilities and everyday amenities are constantly arriving including coffee shops, drug stores, medical offices, new schools (Smiling Creek Elementary opened in 2018), and a future Village Centre; the public library, aquatic complex and Coquitlam Centre is only a short 5 minute drive away.⁣⠀
⁣⠀
Priced from $1.38M including GST.⁣⠀

🆘LOST at Grand Targhee (& offering a REWARD!)💵 // I am missing a set of skis and poles from closing day. The skis are Coalition Snow Abyss powder skis (173cm) with black and orange Look SPX bindings mounted on them (120mm). The poles are white, no idea the brand, but they have been well-used and aren't my main concern.
——
💸💸💸I am offering a $100 REWARD for their safe return, no questions asked!💸💸💸
——
😥I accidentally left them in the parking lot at the end of the day and they were gone when I came back to look about 2 hours later. I am hoping someone grabbed them for me and is trying to find their owner. I had never bought myself a new setup before this and got to use the skis exactly once so am especially bummed about the loss.
——
🎿I have included the one photo I took of me actually wearing them as well as some stock images to better show what they look like.
——
👀I've checked everywhere and they haven't been turned in. I have also posted on local community pages and am keeping an eye on local Craigslist. If anyone seeing this could keep an eye out for someone trying to sell a setup like this, I would really appreciate it! 🙏♥️
——

Combat Engineer (12B)
.
Combat Engineers' mission is to supervise and/or assist team members when tackling rough terrain in combat situations. The combat engineer exhibits expertise in mobility, counter-mobility, survival, and general engineering.
.
You will learn to build defenses to protect the troops or destroy obstacles in the way of combat troops movement. When a water crossing is required, bridges can be built or quickly assembled for both troop and vehicle passage.
.
Job duties include:
.
- Construct fighting positions, fixed/floating bridges, obstacles and defensive positions.
- Place and detonate explosives.
- Conduct operations that include route clearance of obstacles and rivers
- Prepare and install firing systems for demolition and explosives
- Detect mines visually or with mine detectors
.

Here are some photos of our new space!!! 🙌🏻✨🎉
◽️
We’ve been dreaming of this for 7yrs and are so excited!!💞We’ve put our heart and soul into creating it for our community and look forward to the stories of healing and transformation to come. 🙏🏻
◽️
For those wondering...we chose the dragonfly because it is known to represent transformational change! Fun fact: dragonflies also have incredibly adaptive nervous systems that allow them to be one of the most effective hunting insects and cut down on the population of things like mosquitos 🙌🏻😎 ◽️
We’ve found this deep work of healing and growth to completely change our lives and have felt led to share it with and help others reconnect to themselves and bravely choose healing and life. ◽️
If anything about this speaks to you internally, we would love to connect with you and support you. Please reach out at anytime! ◽️
Love to all of you, thank you again for your support!!!

🌸🌸🌸 ↓
⁣
You’ll believe it when you see it. ⁣
Or.... ⁣
You’ll see it when you believe it?⁣
⁣
____________________________________________⁣
⁣
Today I choose not to see a gloomy, grey day. But rather a beautiful day that is revitalizing all those spring flowers and cherry blossom trees with its rain. Giving them life so they can bloom even brighter and bigger on the next sunny day. ⁣
⁣
The same can be applied to our own lives.... You create your own reality, you choose how you see the world. So why not believe that it is full of life, good energy & happiness? Every phase serves a purpose. Without the rainy days we would have no flowers. So instead of choosing to see the grey days as a negative, try to shift your perspective and remember that they are a vital structural component of the sunny days. ⁣
⁣
You’ll see it when you believe it.⁣ 🌸

Did you know that water can aid in weight loss?? We need to drink a lot of water throughout the day and even more if exercising! Here is a great article on this topic. 
Water is an important part of all body functions and processes, including digestion and elimination. When you're on a diet, water also acts as a weight-loss aid because it can help you eat less. "Drinking water is important during weight loss because it provides hydration without unwanted calories. "Drinking water is important during weight loss because it provides hydration without unwanted calories. Drinking non-caloric fluids like water before or with a meal can help a dieter feel full sooner," explains Donna Logan, RD, a registered dietitian at the University of Texas Medical School in Houston. “So in addition to not adding calories, drinking water may help replace or avoid unnecessary food calories found in snacks or extra servings at mealtime. Drinking water also helps flush wastes from the body, which is especially important during times of fat metabolism and weight loss." When it comes to water alone, explains Logan, "A general recommendation is to drink eight 8-ounce cups of water per day, for a total of 64 ounces. This is a generalization only, and actual fluid needs are affected by diet, physical activity, body composition, and climate."
For instance, this number goes up if you exercise — a key to successful weight loss — and even more so in hot weather when it’s possible to lose about the equivalent of a quart of water in an hour, according to the American Council on Exercise. You’ll want to drink water before, during, and after every workout.
Don’t wait to feel thirsty to start sipping — that’s a sign that dehydration has already started to occur. You want to drink water throughout the day, on a regular basis.

2019 has been filled with some pretty amazing adventures, but my favorite by far has been my journey to get back on skis. Over the past month, I’ve been reconnecting with one of my favorite outdoor pastimes as a child, as well as connecting with my favorite mountain in a different way. It hasn’t been the smoothest transition and I still have a little ways to go before I feel comfortable skiing more advanced terrain, but I’m stoked on the progress I’ve made so far and incredibly grateful for my present circumstances that gave me the ability to make it out as often as I have. The season at Meadows is coming to a close so I won’t be able to ski as regularly (😭), but I’m looking forward to continuing this adventure as opportunities arise and maybe even advancing to backcountry in the near future🤞

4.10.2019 | “And just like that, this journey has come to an end. I took this photo yesterday morning as I had a last bittersweet glance of the island that watercolored my dreams in unexpected ways. I came for a cetacean study, but ended up shedding tears as I said goodbye to a place that I feel a deep calling to call home. I’m returning for two or three months on a visa in the fall/winter with @jack__cousteau to scout properties and further research the dual citizenship pathways. While October feels so far from now, the entire idea feels so right. Even I would have never imagined that a front porch would wind up forever changing my course, setting me sail—off transect—in a beautiful new direction. ⚓️
.
Thank you to @naturalist.pt for helping me fall in love with such a special place as soon as I landed in Horta. The front porch of their fisherman’s cabin overlooking Pico and the sea, introductions to an incredible community, perfect weather, dirt cheap feasts, and a rare encounter with orcas were all elements in sealing the deal. But the moment I saw this view, I knew exactly where I belonged. 🐚
.
For now, I have a few more flights before I’m back in the States with my dog and a new dream to set into motion. I’m having a [20-year] tawny Port breakfast in Lisbon, a raclette dinner in Zurich, and the greatest night of sleep just outside D.C.” — @contemporarypilgrim •
.

Friday is finally here and we get so excited because we love sharing our community's weekend happenings for with you all! So, let's jump into all the fun events for you to choose from for your Easter weekend! ⁣⠀
⁣⠀
1. We love that Uptown is always kicking it off with the Summer Series on Friday Nights. Tonight's concert is featuring The River City Horns. Start the weekend with some Rhythm & Blues from 7-10 PM on Broadway.⁣⠀
2. Then wake up to some fresh food, jewelry, & much more as you stroll down uptown at Market Day's on Broadway from 9AM-Noon. @uptowncolumbus 
3. Looking for something a bit more active? Register to run the Campus 2 Campus 8K starting at CSU's baseball fields and finishing at Woodruff Park in Uptown. Registration starts at 6:30AM and the race kicks off at 8AM! @columbusstate ⁣⠀
4. The Annual Callaway Easter Egg Hunt, Fun Runs, & Activities will be perfect for the little ones! Events taking place at Robin Beach from 12-2:30PM with live music. And we heard The Easter Bunny may be making a visit for pictures! @callawaygardens

Went for a big hike last weekend in some morning rain, which made for some very wet trails (some of them were actual little rivers from a hard overnight rain). We hiked between two towns in CT, with a high cliff on one side (Timberlin Trails) and a mountain on the other (Ragged Mountain). By the time we hit the second ascent in the afternoon, though, the skies had cleared and the sun was out. It was our most challenging, yet satisfying, hike to date. 
I'm not a very tall human (and I was among very tall humans) and it was a lot of climbing, ascending, descending, and crossing fast moving streams so I felt like a hobbit in Middle Earth on a quest. I call that hike: "The Battle of The Two Mountains" lol 🤓

Thank you @nas for giving us this master piece 25 years ago. Illmatic is my favorite album of all time. The fact that you grew up within the same area that I did makes this even more special. You’re a inspiration to a lot of us that are from this side of Queens.

When I was about 4 and my older brother was 16 he played this album non stop. Shit he played this album until the tape popped. He probably bought like 2 copies back then lol. I could remember going to sleep to One Love and waking up to One Love. So much to the point @qtiptheabstract voice was stuck in my head lol. Many other songs had that same effect on me too. I didn’t even realize how much of an impact that album had on me at the time. As I got older and listened to the songs again I understood why my brother loved this album so much. 
It was the lyricism, story telling, beats and the album cover that made this album so dope. If somebody came up to me who never listened to hip hop and asked me which hip hop albums they should start with I’d tell them one of the albums you should start with is Illmatic. 
I hope Illmatic had the same Impact on y’all as it did with me. Salute to @nas and thank you again for this 25 year old classic. #illmaticxxv #illmatic #nas #queens #hiphop #queensbridge #astoria #woodside #ravenswood #nyc

Pretty Little Liars (Maldosas no Brasil) é uma série de televisão norte-americana baseada na popular série literária de mesmo nome escrita por Sara Shepard.
.
A série foi protagonizada por Troian Bellisario, Sasha Pieterse, Lucy Hale, Shay Mitchell e Ashley Benson. Ganhou por 5 vezes consecutivas o Prêmio Teen Choice de Melhor Série de TV – Drama.
.
A série se passa três anos desde o desaparecimento de Alison. Spencer, Aria, Hanna e Emily, agora no ensino médio, têm um novo desafio: desvendar mensagens anônimas ameaçando contar seus segredos.
.
Estreou em 8 de junho de 2010 no canal ABC Family. O sucesso de classificações dos primeiros 10 episódios solicitaram que a série literária fosse estendida para além dos 8 primeiros títulos.
.
Em 26 de março de 2013, ABC Family anunciou que um spin-off, Ravenswood, iria ao ar em outubro de 2013. O spin-off foi ao ar com 10 episódios antes de ser cancelado.
.
Em 29 de agosto de 2016, foi oficialmente anunciado o término da série após o fim da sétima temporada. As filmagens da série foram finalizadas em 26 de outubro de 2016.

O último episódio da série foi exibido no dia 27 de junho de 2017, transmitido ao vivo pela emissora Freeform. Todas as temporadas disponíveis no serviço de streaming Netflix.
.
A série tem um segundo spin-off que lançou no dia 20 de março de 2019. Pretty Little Liars: The Perfectionists é baseada no livro The Perfectionists escrito por Sara Shepard. A série conta a história de um outro mistério com adolescentes, e contém as atrizes Sasha Pieterse e Janel Parrish voltado com seus papéis.
.
Espero que tenham gostado de relembrar essa série que marcou muito a minha adolescência 😍 Muitas saudades (principalmente do meu casal #Haleb)
.
🎶 Got a secret, can you keep it? Swear this one you'll save 🎶

Huge thank you to @paulinaroe & @deldia_18 for hosting another awesome book club meet up! . 
This month we read “American Like Me,” by @americaferrera and discussed the meaning behind identity. Swapping stories on experiences, traditions and what it’s like to be perceived in one way by the outside world versus how you see yourself. I personally left feeling inspired by all these woman’s stories. Really taking home the mentality that what people see when they look at me doesn’t matter. At the end of the day, my identity is what I choose it to be. We’re all individuals and we all are in control of our own lives. .
Shoutout to special guest @dgutierreztv & to @chuysresturant for catering. .
If you’d like to join us next month, be sure to follow @paulinaroe and/or @deldia_18 for information on what books were reading next and when the book club meets! All are welcome ♥️

Steph and I absolutely love the ocean and search for new beach getaways as much as possible.  However, we also love to get away to the mountains as much as possible.  Steph is an amazing snowboarder and most guys have a hard tome keeping up with her.  I am an old school skier and most toddlers have no problem passing me like the wind. 🤷‍♀️ That being said, I go to the local mountains almost every weekend during the ski season. My favorite resort is the uncrowded and friendly mountain @snowvalleymtnresort near Lake Arrowhead.  Most locals prefer to go to the crowded and expensive Big Bear or Snow Summit. Not me.  Snow Valley has very reasonable prices and their season passes are the lowest price in the area. I can get there in 1 hour and 45 mins from my beach house to the slopes. This weekend is closing weekend.  We had an epic year for snow this year, so much so that main highway to the resort (and the back way to Big Bear) completely washed away. (**scroll for pics) Special shoutout to @mthighsnow for honoring our passes while the road was repaired. I already can’t wait for next year. ⚡️

Snowbird [snoh•burd] // a person who vacations in or moves to a warmer climate during cold weather
.
We have a lot of "snowbirds" where I'm from - when I hear this term, I mostly think of the older couples I know who have family in different places, or who just love living in the best of both worlds! ⛰🏖 Idaho is gorgeous year-round, but is particularly appealing during the summer for those who aren't fans of the snow. This sketch shows what happens on the other end of the spectrum - rumor has it, Florida is a popular snowbird hangout during the winter ☀️❄

Beautiful end to the week! My client usually likes to have foil work done. This time I talked to her about making it brighter all around and more natural. She has gray hair so we retouched her with #schwarzkopfcolor10 4N and left to process while we painted. We used #oligopro clay lightener, cool toned & extra blonde with 40vol to achieve a beautiful blended highlight. At the end we toned with #matrix Demi permanent 6M. The full process took 3 hours and you would be looking at $150.00-$200.00 depending on the client and what they want to achieve that day. My clients hair will only get better after this first application. It will be healthier and have even more dimension. Call 304.799.6498 to book appointments. I also do free consults at the salon if you have any questions!

Questa foto è di qualche settimana fa, scattata in una delle prime uscite primaverili. In realtà non abbiamo mai smesso di andare a camminare in montagna neanche d'inverno: ogni stagione ha le sue mete e i suoi percorsi più adatti, e le "mezze" sono molto più comode; d'estate quasi sempre ho troppo caldo e mi stanco molto prima. Quello che purtroppo ho proprio mollato quest'anno è la bici da corsa: ci sono andata pochissime volte e per viaggetti brevi. Mi dispiace un sacco e mi manca, ma non ne ho avuto il tempo né la forma necessaria. Rimedierò, non prometto ma spero. Intanto  mi "godo" (per modo di dire) gli ultimi giorni di convalescenza; è per questo che mi sono trovata a parlare di questo argomento: sono bastati pochi giorni chiusa in casa per farmi capire quanto presto sento la mancanza dello stare fuori, all'aperto, alla luce. E pensare che da ragazza ero una lumaca particolarmente pigra 😁 Come si cambia, eh? 😊 .

Thank you to our visitors, members, volunteers and sponsors for another great ski season! This includes our snowmaking team, kitchen help, lift attendants, ski patrollers, lessons instructors, coaches, and everyone else who contributed to this effort. We, the Lebanon Outing Club (LOC) at Storrs Hill Ski Area, hope everyone had fun at the hill this winter, as we sure did! ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Here are some highlights from our 2018-19 season: ·  We installed new lights for night skiing and on our signature star at the top of Storrs Hill! ·  We extended our public ski hours-- adding Tuesday and Thursday evenings, and opening earlier on Saturdays and Sundays! ·  We had nearly 180 participants, kids and adults, participate in our ski and snowboard lessons program! ·  Our Lebanon Outing Club youth ski jumping team had 18 members (ages 4-17), tripling in size over the past three years! ·  Our LOC youth alpine racing team of 10 members learned how to ski race gates with style and speed! ·  We had record turnouts at our Lebanon Outing Club 2019 Ski Jumping Meet, and 2019 Family Fun Night featuring our Annual Cardboard Sled Race! We love seeing so many kids and families out on the hill! ·  We had two pink flamingos join our poma lift line. What better way to mark the places where you can get off the lift! ·  We were home to the Lebanon H.S., Hanover H.S., Kimball Union Academy and Thetford Academy alpine racing teams! We hosted our first, just for fun, Hometown Flannel Race featuring racers from all four schools, as well as Hartford H.S. ·  We opened our new terrain park, Deer Street Park, in February and hosted our First Slopestyle Event in March. ·  We purchased a new groomer, which I like to call “Big Red!” -----
Thanks for your support. Let’s do it again next year!

Stay tuned, as we’ll be busy working on improvements to the hill before we re-open next season.
🔨
📷: Amy Drapeau Olson, @greatrangeframes & Stuart J. Lander.

I don’t shoot a lot of portraiture, but I was pleased with the outcome of this environmental portrait of @diane.hazelwood in the family’s wood-fired sugar shack. The maple syrup operation has been in business for more than half a century, covering three generations. The pride in that history and love of family was evident in Diane’s voice and face as she spoke about the operation and displayed her grandfather’s well-worn sap ladle.

Diane and husband, @arlee_sheets , operate Rock-N-Horse Farm just outside Almonte, Ontario. Over the past year, they have not only opened their barn doors to me as a photographer, but they have become good friends whom we feel fortunate to have met. .

If you are looking for a great place to visit and enjoy some authentic Canadian maple syrup than Gilbertson’s is the place to go! Gilbertson’s Maple Products is one of Ontario’s largest producers of maple syrup. It has been a family run business for over 4 generations! They are located on St. Joseph Island which is about 40 minutes east of Sault Ste. Marie, Ontario.

Waiting on the green of spring, we started reducing some of that sweet maple sap for making a couple more wild fermented sodas. Since we’re new to the scene, we’ve tapped just one tree to get to know the process of sugarbush- and it has been so abundant! We’re not boiling all the way down, just enough to get a sweet thin syrup to sweeten our sodas. Simmering down my meandering recollections of 30 years of adventure into a mere 11 minute film is no easy task, nor is making me look ruggedly cool, but if anyone could either it would be Yeti’s Craig and @joeyschusler to do so. Catch Joey introducing the piece at the festival and watch it on a whopper big screen, beer in hand as it should be appreciated... or if you can’t make Telluride then click the link in my bio. What a treat to ski with Sophie yesterday! It amazes me how time flies. I worked for her papa, Seth, in Vail in the late 90s at Kidstuff Magazine. Since then we've traveled many miles and careers. Two things remain the same - we love skiing & we love kids. And so, one of my fav times of the year is when Seth visits to get his Colorado fix & I get my kiddo fix. Sophie has skied with me since being a wee one as part of Ski Girls Rock. It's an honor to watch her grow.  #sharingtheloveofskiing

Last night was the Willamette Pass Backcountry Ski Patrol party/potluck/ final patrol meeting for the season. This is a great group of caring, fun people who volunteer hundreds of hours because they love the outdoors, winter time recreation and want others to have the best experience too. It’s been a great winter and I’m a little sad this season has ended. 
On a humorous note, I was awarded “Most Enthusiastic”. It’s easy to be enthusiastic about hanging out with awesome people doing fun things. I was also a runner up for the “Bed Pan”award (which is given to a member each year for more dubious achievements.) I was nominated for the Bed Pan for leading a @bergsskishop moonlight snowshoe tour and getting us sort-of-lost.. I realized that these two things sum me up often in life: I don’t always know where I’m going, but I’m making great time! (And usually having a great time too!) #willamettepassbackcountryskipatrol #willamettepass #volunteering #getinvolved #getoutside #getlost

This is a zoomed in shot to show the gorgeous pink light on Mt. Drum.

I wake up at 4am every morning, and despite it occurring every single day, I marvel at the sun each time i catch it at sunrise.  It's one of the only times I realize we are all on a planet spinning around a ball of hot gas. ...in a solar system ...in a whole universe.  And for me..each morning I get to see sunrise, I'm reminded  that the things that I sometimes herald as major problems/concerns are really almost trivial in the grand scheme of life,  and everything else going on in the world, and beyond. ...every morning I do my best to forgive yesterday's mistakes, and trespasses...to reset and appreciate just being alive. ☀️Sunrise is my daily reminder to appreciate every minute I have, and the people I care about. Because tomorrow isnt promised. (Swipe ⬅️🌅) #livefree #youwontmakeitoutalive #dowhatmakesyoufeelgood

Flashback Friday - Finding old photos of learning how to ski dual giant slalom at Squaw Valley when I was 12 or 13.  I picked up skiing fast.  I was a beginner at the beginning of the week skiing at Ski Incline in Incline Village when the instructor told my parents to take me to Squaw Valley where I would be far more challenged.  So they took me to Squaw and I got private lessons in racing on the Marlboro Ski Challenge race course by Red Dog chairlift.  From absolute beginner to racing in under a week!  I credit this to learning how to ice skate at 6 years old.  Ice skating, similar to skiing, deals with learning about edges.

A monumental weekend... today marks Tamar’s 98th day skiing this season... in pursuit of her first “100 Day Pin”. 🙏🏽❤️👊🏽 Skiing 100 days in a season has been a Bucket List goal since losing both her parents, who were avid skiers and introduced Tamar to Aspen as a two year old. Tamar’s father was a member of the 10th Mountain Division in WWII (training here at Camp Hale)... which is ultimately why we call Aspen home today. ❤️ “Aspen; The Pursuit of Happiness” by @toricampisi pretty much says it all.... #aspen #thepursuitofhappiness #toricampisiart #bucketlist #100daypin #ski100days #happywifehappylife #getoutside #lovewhereyoulive #aspenmountain #highlands #snowmass #buttermilk #aspen #aspenvalley #aspencolorado #aspenco #10thmountaindivision #camphale #climbtoglory

We've received some questions about why we've decided not to host a Bonus Weekend, and would like to share the reasons behind this decision: 💬
•
The weekend forecast calls for warm temperatures and rain.  It was great to end the season with 4" of new snow and sunny skies! 😎
•
This Sunday is Easter, and attendance on the mountain is traditionally poor on this day 🐰
•
The Morning Star Chairlift project is already under way!  To ensure that the new high-speed quad is ready for the start of the 2019-20 winter season, our team has already began removing the chairs, as you can see in this photo 🙏
•
Thank you for such a great season!  We'll see you on the mountain this summer! 😎 || #FreshLocalFun #NonProfitAllGood #BogusBasin

Spring is here! Loving our 1st spring in Boise... so here’s a random collection of moments captured while playing outside (mostly training) over the last couple weeks. Liam Ransford, sophomore on my Harbor Springs Rams is really starting to take off.  Learning the width (just over the shaft angle plane in takeaway) a nice turn and plenty of wrist cock ( working on not getting too much wrist cock). A nice inside attack (just under the shaft angle plane) with the club face measured when the shaft is parallel with the ground on the downswing.  Promotes a predictable high draw and that is what Liam is getting here at the driving range at Country Club of Boyne in Harbor Springs, MI.! #golfcoach #golfswing #HarborSprings #Rams #BoyneHighlands #golf #golftips

So i had this head mount for the gopro back when i used to act for "bang bus" & "tug jobs". I decided to give it a whirl while shooting. Anyone have a preference of the POV or the overhead? Does 1 look cooler than the other?
On this series i pocketed the 3 in the corner, had no chance to combo the 9 but i didnt want to knock it away from the pocket for a difficult final shot, so i tried to finesse cue ball by the 9 & it left me a tough shot on the 4. It pays to work on all types of stupid banks just so u have it in ur arsenal. U wouldnt go golfing w just a 7 iron...(unless ur roy McAvoy)

It’s a 300 mile drive and by pure coincidence I just happened to arrive at Willow Lake (a little over 200 miles) just in time to catch the sunset alpenglow on the Wrangell mountains. This is a zoomed in shot to show the gorgeous pink light on Mt. Drum.

I wake up at 4am every morning, and despite it occurring every single day, I marvel at the sun each time i catch it at sunrise.  It's one of the only times I realize we are all on a planet spinning around a ball of hot gas. ...in a solar system ...in a whole universe.  And for me..each morning I get to see sunrise, I'm reminded  that the things that I sometimes herald as major problems/concerns are really almost trivial in the grand scheme of life,  and everything else going on in the world, and beyond. ...every morning I do my best to forgive yesterday's mistakes, and trespasses...to reset and appreciate just being alive. ☀️Sunrise is my daily reminder to appreciate every minute I have, and the people I care about. Because tomorrow isnt promised. (Swipe ⬅️🌅) #livefree #youwontmakeitoutalive #dowhatmakesyoufeelgood

Flashback Friday - Finding old photos of learning how to ski dual giant slalom at Squaw Valley when I was 12 or 13.  I picked up skiing fast.  I was a beginner at the beginning of the week skiing at Ski Incline in Incline Village when the instructor told my parents to take me to Squaw Valley where I would be far more challenged.  So they took me to Squaw and I got private lessons in racing on the Marlboro Ski Challenge race course by Red Dog chairlift.  From absolute beginner to racing in under a week!  I credit this to learning how to ice skate at 6 years old.  Ice skating, similar to skiing, deals with learning about edges.

A monumental weekend... today marks Tamar’s 98th day skiing this season... in pursuit of her first “100 Day Pin”. 🙏🏽❤️👊🏽 Skiing 100 days in a season has been a Bucket List goal since losing both her parents, who were avid skiers and introduced Tamar to Aspen as a two year old. Tamar’s father was a member of the 10th Mountain Division in WWII (training here at Camp Hale)... which is ultimately why we call Aspen home today. ❤️ “Aspen; The Pursuit of Happiness” by @toricampisi pretty much says it all.... #aspen #thepursuitofhappiness #toricampisiart #bucketlist #100daypin #ski100days #happywifehappylife #getoutside #lovewhereyoulive #aspenmountain #highlands #snowmass #buttermilk #aspen #aspenvalley #aspencolorado #aspenco #10thmountaindivision #camphale #climbtoglory

We've received some questions about why we've decided not to host a Bonus Weekend, and would like to share the reasons behind this decision: 💬
•
The weekend forecast calls for warm temperatures and rain.  It was great to end the season with 4" of new snow and sunny skies! 😎
•
This Sunday is Easter, and attendance on the mountain is traditionally poor on this day 🐰
•
The Morning Star Chairlift project is already under way!  To ensure that the new high-speed quad is ready for the start of the 2019-20 winter season, our team has already began removing the chairs, as you can see in this photo 🙏
•
Thank you for such a great season!  We'll see you on the mountain this summer! 😎 || #FreshLocalFun #NonProfitAllGood #BogusBasin

Liam Ransford, sophomore on my Harbor Springs Rams is really starting to take off.  Learning the width (just over the shaft angle plane in takeaway) a nice turn and plenty of wrist cock ( working on not getting too much wrist cock). A nice inside attack (just under the shaft angle plane) with the club face measured when the shaft is parallel with the ground on the downswing.  Promotes a predictable high draw and that is what Liam is getting here at the driving range at Country Club of Boyne in Harbor Springs, MI.! #golfcoach #golfswing #HarborSprings #Rams #BoyneHighlands #golf #golftips

So i had this head mount for the gopro back when i used to act for "bang bus" & "tug jobs". I decided to give it a whirl while shooting. Anyone have a preference of the POV or the overhead? Does 1 look cooler than the other?
On this series i pocketed the 3 in the corner, had no chance to combo the 9 but i didnt want to knock it away from the pocket for a difficult final shot, so i tried to finesse cue ball by the 9 & it left me a tough shot on the 4. It pays to work on all types of stupid banks just so u have it in ur arsenal. U wouldnt go golfing w just a 7 iron...(unless ur roy McAvoy)

Pictures like these look simple but they tell a story of a conversation or moment someone at the gym learned valuable information.... Ryan grabbed me before starting his training and asked me about correct form in something he was doing......it ended up turning into a lecture from me that made him take a step backwards in order to take two steps forward.

A real gym is not just a room with equipment and people wearing uniforms  that don't know shit.....A gym should be where you go to build yourself and it becomes part of the reason you became what you never would have on your own.

Worker-owned, Local farm-to-table  @Littlegrillcollective delivered on the very best vegan meal of our trip to the valley.

Nachos Supreme: House-made tortilla chips, vegan nacho sauce, veggie chili, lettuce, pickled red onions, and avocado creme.

Lambert’s Platter: Tofu scrambler, fried spicy Cajun potatoes covered in mushroom gravy, and vegan soysage (tasted oddly similar to our buckwheat pancakes, so I suspect it was a grain base)

Local Buckwheat pancakes: Made with Wade's Mill buckwheat, rice flour, agave, Edgewood Farms molasses, almond milk, and flax. Enjoyed with a bit of sorghum syrup

visits #stacksmtpleasant with deja vu, a great environment, and our very prestigious and special guest, Barbara Franklin with Franklin & Associates. Thank you for joining us Barbara, you are a wealth of knowledge and experience!

Stacks is a quaint and peaceful restaurant off of Ben Sawyer Blvd hiding away with a little sign to guide you through their doors.

Walking in created a sense of deja vu for us, as it reminded us heavily of another restaurant, much to our delight! 
Being the classic image of a sandwhich shop, I got their “Turkey Cran” sandwhich- Coleslaw, turkey breast, cranberry, and swiss cheese all in one delicious bite. They offer soups and chips, but honestly this was enough on its own, and the best kind of messy!

Considering we spoke for nearly 30 minutes at one of their tables before we ordered anything, their food was amazing, and the environment perfect, Stacks will definitely be added to our revisit list. Keep it up!!!! 🔹
😇

Q & A with our plastic surgeon, the beyond talented Dr. Hensel. 👨‍⚕️ 1️⃣ What do you do at LPSC?  I am a board certified plastic surgeon specializing in facial and body contouring .
2️⃣ What is your favorite food?  Brisket. Hands down.
.
3️⃣ What are 3 activities/things you enjoy BESIDES surgery? - Spending time with my family - Scuba diving - Traveling
.
4️⃣ What are 3 random facts about yourself? - My grandmother was a pilot - I’m a pilot myself and had my grandmother’s plane at one point in my life - I’ve been on the Keto diet for over 3 years and kept off the 55 lbs I lost with it! .
5️⃣ What is your favorite procedure?  I love all the procedure I preform. Breast augmentations, mommy makeovers, tummy tucks, facelifts, eye lifts... all of it!
.
6️⃣ Why do you love working here?  I love being a plastic surgeon and the ability to share my expertise with women and men around the world. It is beyond gratifying and a source of pride for me to help people look and feel their best.

Combat Engineer (12B)
.
Combat Engineers' mission is to supervise and/or assist team members when tackling rough terrain in combat situations. The combat engineer exhibits expertise in mobility, counter-mobility, survival, and general engineering.
.
You will learn to build defenses to protect the troops or destroy obstacles in the way of combat troops movement. When a water crossing is required, bridges can be built or quickly assembled for both troop and vehicle passage.
.
Job duties include:
.
- Construct fighting positions, fixed/floating bridges, obstacles and defensive positions.
- Place and detonate explosives.
- Conduct operations that include route clearance of obstacles and rivers
- Prepare and install firing systems for demolition and explosives
- Detect mines visually or with mine detectors
.

Suzy Chafee -
Born Rutland, Vermont, November 29, 1946. Member of the Mammoth Mountain Ski Club today.
1968 Captain of the women’s team of the US Olympic Ski Team, Grenoble, France. 3-time world free skiing champion, 1971-73. She was the first woman to serve on the US Olympic Committee, and a champion of Title IX. Inducted into the National Ski Hall of Fame in 1988. •

Last year I was some days in Ribeirinha do Pico, at
Marjella and Mart's place, the Barro & Barro Atelier (@barrobarropottery )where art and nature are always around. I discovered they work from close and I had the privilege of register with documentary photography, step by step, the different technics and tools that they use for the pottery products, with special attention on the raku technic
....................
El año pasado estuve unos días en Ribeirinha do Pico, en
el sítio de Marjella y Mart, Barro & Barro Atelier, donde arte y naturaleza están siempre alrededor. Descubrí su trabajo de cerca y tuve el privilegio de registrar con fotografía documental, paso a paso, las diferentes técnicas y herramientas que utilizan para los productos de cerámica, con especial atención en la técnica del raku.

Y'all this one is complicated. After she was killed and her body co-opted by Sasquatch she got cloned and resurrected in the pages of Wolverine. Because these things happen. She didn't get killed off with the rest of the team though when they fought the collective. .
.Later, Snowbird is sent by her Grandfather Hodiak to join Athena's God-Squad in order to defeat the Skrull deities Sl'gur't and Kly'bn. While traveling the Skrulls assimilated Gods, Snow Bird decided to end her loneliness by sleeping with Hercules. During a battle with a group of skrull gods, she transforms to Neooqtoq the Ravager, deadliest of the Great beast of the North, for a long time and loses her mind, consequently killing anything in her way. At the last moment she transformed to a cloud of mosquitoes, honoring her fallen comrades by fighting on. She returns and impales the skrull god Kly'bn on the spine of the slain God-eater Demogorge. At the end, she carries a weeping Hercules and Amadeus back to earth in the form of a Great White bird. .
.
Then I lost her again until the new series.  She appears to have joined the space flight but stays on Earth.  Here she is in her team uniform.

We had questions for our Cali member Frank (@franklinlin17) , and here’s what he had to say! ⁣
⁣
Q: What inspired you to begin snowboarding? 🏂⁣
⁣
A: I started snowboarding because it looked cool! I skied as a kid but I’m high school, started snowboarding and fell in love with it. Plus, my snowboard instructor had an Australian accent and was mesmerized by his voice 😜⁣
⁣
Q: What was the hardest thing to learn when you first started? 😬⁣
⁣
A: Connecting my turns to carve! Being 6’3”, it’s definitely more challenging. Also, getting over the fear of going fast. Still working on that! ⁣
⁣
Q: When it’s a day in the mountains, 🏔 how do you like to start and end the day?⁣
⁣
A: When I begin a day, I like to do a few warm up runs before heading up to the top.⁣
⁣
When I finish a day on the slopes, I like to jump in the hot tub with a stiff drink to relax and unwind. 😊⁣
⁣
⁣

This is me
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
. .
.  If you know me then you may be familiar with what makes me happy. This vacation will soon come to an end but these experiences have made me happy and that makes me feel successful.  #MilesOfSmiles has been maximized to the fullest.  Rather than a “$” sign, my success can be measured in miles.. here’s just a recap of the last 5 days:  150miles on my first Harley ride through Lake Mead to the Hoover Dam in Arizona. 200miles in a slingshot to the Valley of Fire, Nevada. Another 240miles from Las Vegas to Red Rock Canyon, NV and through Death Valley, California (and a quick pit stop to Area 51 👽). Then to end the last two days experiencing a Cadillac V Performance academy with professional drivers teaching new skills on the track.  I couldn’t ask for a cooler person to experience all this with. He’s the fun person I can laugh with and laugh at, my teacher that encourages me through a steep hill or tight turns on a bike, and most of all he’s my husband who I am lucky enough to call my best friend @adamtherealhopper .  Thanks for reading... raise your hand 🖐🏽, did you really read this? no? I understand. 😂  #harleydavidson #lowrider #motorcycle #rider #ladyrider #bikerbabes #slingshot #tyedye #turtle #adventuresofaturtle #cadillac #cadillacctsv #lakemead #hooverdam #valleyoffire #redrockcanyon #deathvalley #area51 #lasvegas #nevada #arizona #california #racingschool  honorable mentions: #GordonRamsey best food experience EVER #PennAndTeller must see! #SpringMountain on the way to Death Valley there was a road (6th pic) NO ONE was on, straight road that disappeared on the horizon, we were so far into the desert we could just hop out of the car with no one around for miles. These are the experiences that will become memories that I will cherish forever. #godisgood

Expect really good fruit with intense, complex flavors and deep color.

Lost but not forgotten. Unbound from its former label. I found this little badass time traveler deep within a cellar in San Francisco. Perhaps one of the most edifying and inspirational wines I have ever had the privilege to drink. First hour is nothing but graphite and green herb and saddle bag. Then came the brilliant sweet damp earth, the rich red iron petrichor, and an ethereal brightness that’s hard to believe. The ‘78 Cheval Blanc is an all timer. Joined by the ‘79 Keenan for a left bank contrast, a worthy dance partner. #keenanwinery #springmountain #napavalley #chevalblanc #stemillion #rightbank #leftbank

My spiritual practice is not about accessing some space that transcends my current human condition. It is not about denying any experience whether internal or external. It's not about honoring some god that is greater than myself. It's about collaborating with the deepest, most intelligent, intentional and creative parts of my own Self. It's about meeting myself where I'm at while acknowledging that my potential is beyond what I could ever imagine. It's about creating the space for that potential to rise to the surface and it's about staying grounded enough to make sure that my action is aligned with what is best for myself and the world. It's about maintaing a level of subtle wellness that allows me to process all of the experiences that I have so that I am not accumulating traumas that cloud my perception. It's about being able to gracefully move from my head to my heart and back again. That's all. 😀
.
.
.

Now, an Epic Pass can be purchased for up to seven individual days of unrestricted access to slopes at popular resorts including Breckenridge, Vail, Whistler Blackcomb, Park City, and other North American resorts. For passes of 4 days or more, you’ll have access to Telluride, Snowbasin, Sun Valley, and six additional Canadian resorts. Excited to announce I just finished up my last contract as a travel and tele nurse!! I’ve decided to put down some roots in Reno and will start my new perm job in the ICU soon!!! ✨
Since I started traveling, I have met amazing people, created incredible memories, and have learned more about myself than I could’ve ever imagined. It feels a little bittersweet to say goodbye to this adventure I’ve been on the last couple of years. ✨
But I’ve wanted to be an ICU nurse since I started nursing school and am beyond excited to finally realize this dream! I love the life I’m building here in Reno and am excited to be able to really settle in here. Plus, who could leave a place this beautiful?! I love the mountains and Tahoe way too much! So let me know if you wanna come visit- I’ll be here 😊

We’ve always done an Easter hike- while I deeply miss Oakley, it’s been a joy to see Paddington embracing a life with me solo. Oakley used to be the one that stopped, waited and checked for me on the trail- now Paddington does this. Paddington sure was holding back so his brother could be the leader. Paddington even gave me a heartfelt hello upon me return home, Oakley always used to dominate the greetings. I miss Oakley but this new relationship building with Paddington is bringing a lot of joy to my heart.

House plants are at the top of everyone's shopping list this Spring. It's important to know the basics of plant care before adding them to your home.

Choose Plants Based on Light in your Space
Are the plants you love the ones you can have? The​ available light in your space will help you decide. Check the direction your windows are facing; south-facing windows give bright light, east/west-facing windows give moderate light and north-facing windows give low light. Most houseplants prefer bright, indirect sunlight.

Figure Out Your Plant Compatibility
New to plant parenthood? A busy ​work schedule, social​ ​life and general forgetfulness can lead to unintentional plant neglect. It’s okay. Some plants can handle that kind of lifestyle. A jetsetter like yourself will enjoy the resilience of low-maintenance succulents, ZZ plants or snake plants, all pretty low key, as long as they have enough light (bright and low light respectively). Raise the Humidity Levels
Staying true to your plants natural environment will help your plant thrive indoors. Most tropical plants, ferns and orchids prefer high humidity and bright to moderate, indirect light. Mist these plants in between waterings with filtered water.

Source: thesill.com

Pool sharpens the mind & puts ur creative problem solving to the test many times per rack. God i love this gm.

Vamos falar um pouquinho do que usar quando for esquiar! ⛸️
Eu recomendo roupas impermeáveis SEMPRE! 
Calça, jaqueta e luvas essas peças devem ser próprias, elas são de tecido de alta tecnologia, possuem isolamento térmico e impermeabilidade. 🧥👖🧤 .
(Dica extra: quanto mais bolso sua jaqueta e calça tiver melhor!)
Touca, óculos escuros e cachecol  também não podem faltar. 🧦🧣 .
E uma dica super importante: muito protetor solar, tanto no rosto como para os lábios! O reflexo do sol e até mesmo o mormaço reflete na neve branca e queima muito. Mesmo nos dias de temperatura baixa, sempre use protetor! Lembre-se que no frio a pele fica seca e por isso usar hidratante também é importante. ⛄⛷ .

For my first #SmallBusinessSaturday feature, I’m happy to share @eaglepointfarm_853 with you!
•
This quaint farmer’s market in Trexlertown offers everything from gorgeous fresh flowers to local honey and fresh produce.
•
I’ve been looking for a local and ethical source of eggs and stumbled upon @the_nesting_box. They’re a little bit of a hike for me to make this weekend and I was delighted to find that Eagle Point carries their farm fresh eggs! I love that I can see pictures and videos of the beautiful hens that are laying these precious eggs. I even saw a little hen feather fluff on one of the eggs - so cute!
• 
I don’t drink milk too often but my boyfriend is a milkaholic. Eagle Point carries local dairy from Way-Har Farms in Bernville. It is DELICIOUS!
• 
Not only were the flowers gorgeous but I really appreciated the way the shop is set up. Everything is so beautifully displayed and the owners were so kind and helpful. This was a great experience and I can’t wait to visit again. I encourage you to swing by and support local farmers!!

We like trails, you like trails, we ALL like trails! MMBTS is on the gas right now to get the new jump trail going on Moose. We are excited that between us and the excellent folks at Devinci we are giving away a SPARTON CARBON NX! Devinci has always been a huge supporter of our local trails and have helped us raise tens of thousands of dollars in the past for MMBTS, CMBA and GWBCTA. 
For your chance to win, come by any one of the shops and buy a ticket. $10 gets you entered in to win a $5400 carbon trail eating machine. The draw will happen at the end of June so do not delay. 
All ticket proceeds go to MMBTS to support the trail build. Look for Calgary Cycle at the trailhead where we will also have tickets for sale.  See you out in the sticks and let’s get this trail built!

Today, many celebrate the Lord's resurrection from the dead. Maybe in your reverent observation you also consider the not-so-evident and decidedly less significant meaning in the story.
.
I mean where life's twisted misfortunes drag you to wits end and pitch literal death as a valid escape. Some people will never know this low, where you feel like a suffocating soul that the devil just won't claim.
.
The point is that, paradoxically, tragedy and heartbreak allude to a deeper truth in life.
.
Beyond “suffering builds character”.
.
No doubt the darkest tragedies are those in which the death of something is literally the end of the line. While writing today, I thought the illustration of a soul CLINGING tenaciously to their resentment, fear, old thought paradigms, and pain portrayed this well. They’re dead ends in themselves.
.
But there’s also death in the LETTING GO. And I think that’s the transformative power of it. Maybe that’s why the human mind resorts to terminal thinking when feelings of “this hopeless story arc doesn’t need to continue”. Instinctively, we KNOW something has to change. We are ALIVE by nature.
.
But if we can find the courage to let go, 
That’s where the universe breathes new life into you.
Redemption.
Redefinition.
Vibrance.
Clarity.
.
So here’s to the that courage...
That in spite of feeling apprehensive by a brilliant, beckoning unknown, you take hope by the hand, inhale, and put one foot forward.
.
Open your eyes to a world unseen.
Here’s to resurrection.
Here’s to rebirth.
Here’s to beauty reframed in new light.
You’ve done this before.
.
Happy Easter.
May what’s dying in you reassemble.
.
.
.

This weekend we celebrate so many things.  The Resurrection.  My Hudson’s 14th birthday (four tweezy baby). Selling a house.  The big peach crop that’s coming.  And my parent’s 50th wedding anniversary.  If you know them, you love them.  If you love me, you love them.  They are spectacular in every sense of the word and are living examples of what’s right in this world.  Of course we celebrated by renting two RV’s and camping all weekend.  Dad claimed it was her “dream”. Mom denied it but we all had the best time.  So blessed to call them my parents.

Call me crazy but I left the beach and drove through 91 degree heat to the mountains where it was 70 degrees and the snow was melting at a breakneck pace.  My favorite little local resort @snowvalleymtnresort promised they would be open through Easter and they kept their promise by pushing just enough snow around to keep the slopes open. Don’t judge this awesome resort by these pictures.  We had an epic year of snow after the severe draught that California went through in the last few years.  It takes me an hour and 45 minutes from my beach house to the slopes and it’s made me love skiing again!  I can’t wait for next year! ❄️ ❄️

Closing weekend at @snowvalleymtnresort ! They promised to stay open until Easter weekend and they delivered their promise as usual.  I love this little resort.  They have so much heart and are way less crowded than surrounding ski resorts.  I’ve dragged so many friends up there that it’s starting to get crowded. It isn’t easy keeping snow in our local mountains and no one tries harder than Snow Valley Mountain Resort to maintain a great experience for us.  It wasn’t perfect but I had a blast anyway.  Thanks @jherguth being the only other person who is willing to snowboard in 70 degrees!  Scroll to the ducks wading in the melted snow. 🦆 ⚡️ Can’t wait for next year! #snowvalley #lakearrowhead #skiing #snowboarding #myhappyplace

Yesterday was Iskigamizige Giizis, the Sugar Moon. I think it's very natural that this moon comes right after the Onaabani Giizas, the Hard Crust Moon. The fourth moon of creation celebrates the maple sap beginning to run, as we harvest and share one of the main medicines given to our people the Anishinaabe. As sap begins to run stickly down the maple trees, it signals the end of Winter and the new birth of Spring. 🌷🍁 #anishinaabe #ojibwe #baymillsindiancommunity #indigenous #destinationbaymills #bmic #traditionalteachings #sugarbush #storytelling

Happy Easter to all who celebrate! We ended our day on an amazing sunset. As we began our downsized journey I thought holidays would be the hardest. Although I'm not much of a shopper or a decorator. 
I actually have enjoyed the holidays more with a downsized mentality. No fuss. No stress! The girls even shared an Easter basket. While the Easter bunny did not fill a basket for them, we went to 2 community egg hunts that they loved. We made snow bunnies (because apparently winter is holding on for dear life). We took a family walk and made dinner together. 
Not having space for more stuff makes you realize how unimportant all of the stuff really is. Downsizing is not for everyone. With that in mind, we hope everyone enjoyed their day no matter how you celebrate!

🌎 Happy Earth Day! 🌎 This picture was taken at Lower Mohawk Lake in Breckenridge, Colorado. It stands at 11,680 ft. above sea level. ⠀
⠀
🌲🏔🌲🏔I hiked 7 miles through the most stunning landscape, short of breath and with an an aching ankle. As the elevation got higher and the trail steeper, I almost gave up. But when I reached the top, the scene actually took my breath away. It was indescribably peaceful. A feeling that affected me to my core.⠀
⠀
As you scroll through your feeds and see the countless Earth Day posts, let it serve as a reminder to make every day Earth Day. Because let me tell you, this beautiful blue planet is worth fighting for! ✨⠀

From #Roll42

This came from one of my latest rolls of #Ektachrome100 slide film! My buddy and I went snowboarding for the day in February 2019. Slide film is less forgiving in terms of exposure than color negative film, but when you nail it, it looks fantastic!
I've had good results using my camera's built in light meter, set to matrix metering. I developed this film at home and scanned it using my tablet as a light source and a DSLR as a scanner. I took 9 shots of each frame and stitched them together to create the final, high resolution image.

Thankful to be able to experience stuff like this. Earth in it's raw form really brings out the best of everything. Every emotion you could imagine, from pure adrenaline to tears of joy at the summit, to even being downright terrified with 4,000 feet of air underneath your heels. The wind whipping your face, the rocks pelting you, the crevasses below waiting to swallow you whole. Something you definitely have to respect and appreciate. Places like this really put you in the most pure form of living and we should all treat the planet better so places like this can exist for future generations.

7 mile walk to begin training regimen for my June through October hiking plans. Going to try for 24 Cascade volcanoes all over 7,000 feet. Completed only 4 of the 28 last Summer/Fall after some work interruptions with my plans
.
8 of them are hike summit capable:
-Mt. Saint Helens (8363 feet)
-South Sister (10358 feet)
-Mt. Bachelor (9069 feet)
-Diamond Peak (8744 feet)
-Mt. Bailey (8368 feet)
-Mt. Thielson (9184 feet)
-Mt. McLoughlin (9495 feet)
-Broken Top (9055 feet)
.
Photos: @chateauduphenix (2019)
Location: St. Johns, Portland, OR

He's extremely knowledgeable & nice. His attention to detail & pride in his work truly shows.
🧡

Ну вот настал очередной счастливый день , Охотничья гора , уютненький американский бар , живой Джаз, довольно покачивающиеся головы людей в такт музыке , огромнейший пэнкэйк с сочною клубникой сверху , мои раскрасневшиеся от тепла щеки , высочайшие снежные спуски , сегодня я покорила всего лишь небольшой спуск и то упала несколько раз , причём довольно больновато ...Хмуро  морщишь лицо , переворачиваешься на живот и снова поднимаешься , в этом вся прелесть жизни , не имеет значения сколько раз ты падал , главное сколько раз поднимался ... Сегодня очень ветрено , люди смело поднимаются на фуникулерах и весело направляются к назначению точки  х ... Заснеженные горы , среди тёмного леса деревьев пробиваются вечнозеленые ели , так и тянуться макушками к небу , красота безумная вокруг , а ты ? А ты просто счастлив , потому что сбылась ещё одна мечта , даже ноги гудят не от усталости , а от счастья ... 💚🌍❄️#huntermountain #lastdayofwinter #theendofseason #happynessiseverywhere #snowboarding🏂 #mynewhobby #happychild 🥁⛰💙

To This Earth We Must Go

As tall mountains we do climb,
Knowing we do not have much time.
Let us savor the sublime,
This earthen beauty we call mine.

As pollution grows so fast,
Please do learn from the past,
Or the trees and rocks will be surpassed,
This Earth will not forever last.

As wind and storm may rage along,
And make music by their song,
Let us not waver long,
This Earth must live on.

As the rivers never cease to flow,
Through the trees and from the snow,
To the Ocean far below,
To this earth We must go.

Sports Illustrated called the Ford Family the "Wizards of Wappoo". The Easter Lamb is a typical Easter cake from the municipality of Favara in Sicily, made of almond or pistachio paste, dating back to the 19th century. This tradition is closely connected to the making of ‘Frutta Martorana,’ the traditional marzipan (a.k.a. almond paste) sweets, in the form of realistic fruits and vegetables from the provinces of Palermo and Messina in Sicily.

With as much as we travel (for work and play) we start to view hotels with a different lens. A hotel becomes your home away from home and is critical to your good night’s rest, comfort, and becomes your home base. @thedewberrycharleston was a breath of fresh air and somewhere we became so fond of. If only all hotels held themselves to the level of amazing service, cleanliness, and authenticity of providing a true experience as The Dewberry does. 
HOTEL TIPS: Make sure you rent (complimentary) their bikes to ride around town, reserve a spot ahead of time at their rooftop bar The Citrus Club (we love the piña coladas!), and don’t forget to stop into The Living Room for drinks (after 3pm) - seen here is a cocktail called The Panic Button, the entire hotel has a Mad Men vibe (hey Don Draper). The hotel has town cars that will provide complimentary drop off around town 
FOOD: Favorite restaurant in town was @basic_kitchen a lovely take on healthy meets date night out or for smoothies, @cleanjuice and for seafood, @eattheordinary oh and don’t forget BBQ at @lewisbarbecue as well as @theobstinatedaughter for brunch and @saltcowboys for drinks on the water 
SEE/DO: Middleton Plantation if the weather is great, Kiawah island if you’re up for a bit of a drive, kayak Shem’s Creek and look for dolphins, bike to The Battery and do a walking house tour of historic spots in the area, beach day at Sullivan’s Island .

I can't think of a clever pun and I falafel about it... It's a beautiful and nice long weekend, so I (Beck) took a little walk and went to @nubatown, tucked in a small street off of Main. I've never been, but my oh my, it just became one of those places I will constantly be craving. Offering fresh and healthy Lebanese food, many of their dishes are vegetarian/vegan friendly and gluten-free.

Sharing the Najib's Special lunch plate and a Chicken Tawook pita wrap (switched out the chicken with tempeh), it was super filling in the best way possible. The crispy cauliflower of the Najib's special was crisp to perfection, with plenty of flavour, and a delightful pairing when eaten with the hummus and brown rice. And my personal favourite part was the garlic sauce of the Tawook--I love anything with garlic, but that sauce really made the dish for me. And that's the tea.

Rating: 9.5/10

Happy Easter from our neighborhood to yours! This adorable little family let us get up close and personal. They may have known that we are animal lovers and would never hurt them, or they may have just been hungry for the pancakes we brought. The world may never know. We have had a family of geese visit us for the past three years and I can't help but think that they return to us year after year because they too feel that Mt. Pleasant is a great place to raise a family. .

7 mile walk to begin training regimen for my June through October hiking plans. Going to try for 24 Cascade volcanoes all over 7,000 feet. Completed only 4 of the 28 last Summer/Fall after some work interruptions with my plans
.
8 of them are hike summit capable:
-Mt. Saint Helens (8363 feet)
-South Sister (10358 feet)
-Mt. Bachelor (9069 feet)
-Diamond Peak (8744 feet)
-Mt. Bailey (8368 feet)
-Mt. Thielson (9184 feet)
-Mt. McLoughlin (9495 feet)
-Broken Top (9055 feet)
.
Photos: @chateauduphenix (2019)
Location: St. Johns, Portland, OR

California has been full of amazing adventures, and I’m so proud of myself for showing up with everything I’ve had for them. It helps a lot to have a great adventure buddy with so much experience in @ryzielovessnow, and while sometimes my inexperience has held him back on these big mountains, he’s been my biggest supporter and it’s amazing to get to do these things together. Backcountry snowboarding is so rewarding, from the hours in the mountains that include seeing the hills light up in sunrise alpenglow to the feeling of happy, exhausted stoke after using crampons for the first time and riding my first big chute to so much more than I can say in a single post with a single photo. So for now, gratitude.

Happy Earth Day! Can you believe our beautiful world does this every morning? The red color is due to alpenglow - when the solar disk is just below the horizon, opposite of the glow. Being bathed in alpenglow is a transcendent experience, especially after having trekked across frozen lakes under moonlight and an alarm set for 1:00 AM. I have always found Sky Pond to be the stuff of the heavens, and this couldn’t be more true at dawn.

Happy Earth Day
—————————
In 2014 one of my dear friends got married in Telluride, Colorado. A few days before the nuptials we embarked on a hike to Blue Lakes. But due to some cavalier flippancy on my part, we unwittingly took the left fork in the trail, eventually depositing us to Blaine Basin. What a fortunate error this turned out to be. I’ve been back to Blaine Basin a few times since. It’s possibly my all-time favorite slice of backcountry. On my last visit I spent the night and had the entirety of the basin all to myself. So when you pull up to the trailhead after a dozen or so miles on rutted out roads and see 30 cars, fear not as 29 of them will likely be heading towards Blue Lakes, but you’ll be heading towards the incomparable Blaine Basin.
.
.
.

This Earth Day, I'm not just thinking about our planet and the ecosystems that are radically changing as a result of our actions—I'm also thinking about the mass bombings in Sri Lanka, the three world-class climbers who died in an avalanche in Banff National Park, the mosque attacks in Christchurch, New Zealand, the results of Alberta's latest election and the environmental policies that are being repealed or altered as a result of conservative governments the world over. We are living in a volatile climate politically, socially and environmentally, and when there is so much that happens every day on our Earth that shocks us to our core, it can be hard to remain hopeful, positive & optimistic. These problems existed before many of us came to be alive, and they will continue to exist when we are gone—but if you're wondering how on Earth anything you do is going to make a world of difference, perhaps you can remember the words of Margaret Mead: ”Never doubt that a small group of thoughtful, committed citizens can change the world; indeed, it's the only thing that ever has.”⁣

Brown Brothers 3.5⭐️
Venue stunning. Tasting room old school, but well set up for groups. Wines and service good, not great.

Two restaurants- a lovely casual share plate focused “wine bar” or the high end “Patricia” which I haven’t experienced but apparently excellent.

I just love the vibe of this whole region. It’s relaxed and spacious. A refreshing change from some wine areas which can be stuffy, pretentious or intimidating.
✅Stunning place to spend the day
✅Their version of a pre-mixed spritz I actually decent.
❌ indoor spaces are pretty dated.

Brown Brothers 3.5⭐️
Venue stunning. Tasting room old school, but well set up for groups. Wines and service good, not great.

Two restaurants- a lovely casual share plate focused “wine bar” or the high end “Patricia” which I haven’t experienced but apparently excellent.

I just love the vibe of this whole region. It’s relaxed and spacious. A refreshing change from some wine areas which can be stuffy, pretentious or intimidating.
✅Stunning place to spend the day
✅Their version of a pre-mixed spritz I actually decent.
❌ indoor spaces are pretty dated.

Tribute Tuesday • Elizabell Williams • Hall of Fame Class of 1996 • Sport Builder

Willie, as she was affectionately known by her "kids", was born in Lockhard, Texas and raised in San Antonio. The Rockies drew her to Colorado, when she came here to work as a nurse for the Children's Hospital in Denver.

It was Willie's love for children that led her to coordinate a skiing program, with the assistance of Children's Hospital, for young patients with limb amputations.

The first program of 17 boys was held at Arapahoe Basin in January 1968, with the help of Willy Schaeffler and Ski School head Ed Lucks. Willie also recruited the volunteered to assist in this program. Those volunteers, with Willie's leadership, created what has become the model most adaptive programs are based upon today.

To quote Willie, "How can a child consider himself handicapped when he can ski as well or better than his two-legged friends? They can ski circles around me. Their smiling faces and determined attitudes say more than words could ever express." With this attitude behind her, she forged on. She approached the ski industry for help and was given overwhelming support in supplying ski equipment.

In 1970-1971, the Three Track Ski Club moved to the Winter Park Ski Area, where Hal O'Leary took on the program. This was the beginning of the internationally acclaimed National Sports Center for the Disabled (NSCD). Willie and Hal developed and trained skiers who eventually became World Champions in disabled skiing.

Willie pursued her commitment to disabled skiing, and as the program grew, she was involved in many national events, culminated in 1980 when she accompanied the U.S. Disabled Team to the International Winter Paralympics in Geilo, Norway.

She was also instrumental in producing three instructional and inspirational films featuring skiing and outdoor recreational activities for children with physical disabilities. Fortunately through the NSCD, and the support of Winter Park, her vision lives on.

Today was the first day in a few years that I didn’t spend this date around waterfalls or spring flowers. It was a Monday, I had to go to work. My job isn’t a hard one but the hardest part for me is watching the single use products go out the door that I know will most likely hit the landfill or worse, our landscapes. 
Seeing the same faces every day - some multiple times a day - getting the same drink, in the same size, that they will probably toss in the same trashcan that they do every day after their commute to work.
I did hear a few more people than normal ask for ceramic mugs today, but if they were doing that to ‘celebrate Earth Day’ I hope they realize that Earth Day should be everyday.
It’s time to change the routine, people.
Get a reusable cup, straw, grocery bag, literally anything to reduce your waste. 
I’m not saying this is the only or even the biggest problem, and I’m not about to argue the “but what about...” But we’ve gotta start somewhere and if you think it doesn’t start with you, then you’re sadly mistaken. 
#EarthDay

Celebrating Earth Day 🌍 by reflecting on all of the experiences I have been fortunate enough to have had in the past year. I spent 2018 seeing temples in Bangkok, wandering Singapore’s Botanic Gardens in a thunder storm, watching the sun set over a rice paddy field in Cambodia with strangers and cold beer, seeing trees grow within temple ruins, atv-ing in the Palm Springs Desert and then taking the tram to 8516 feet up into the forested mountains, getting up close to a Joshua Tree and and peeking through tourists to see Skull Rock, and ended the year skiing for the first time with friends in Michigan. This earth is beautiful in every way and we need to treat it well. We need to be cautious, and calculated in our choices as everything we do has and impact and leaves behind a footprint. Last year after being vegetarian for 8 years I made the choice to go vegan with the environmental impact I would be making being a driving factor, and this year my goal has been to dramatically reduce my use of single use products and my overall waste. I want to be able to see so much of this world and I want to see it in all of its beauty, so I’m doing what I can to keep it thriving. 🌿🌍 #earthday #happyearthday #earthday2019 #climatechange #vegan #explore #travel #southeastasia #cambodia #thailand #singapore #joshuatree #palmsprings #desert #atv #michigan #boynemountain

While hiking, leave no trace and make sure we’re leaving the trails better than we found them! Thankful to be able to experience stuff like this. Earth in it's raw form really brings out the best of everything. Every emotion you could imagine, from pure adrenaline to tears of joy at the summit, to even being downright terrified with 4,000 feet of air underneath your heels. The wind whipping your face, the rocks pelting you, the crevasses below waiting to swallow you whole. Something you definitely have to respect and appreciate. Places like this really put you in the most pure form of living and we should all treat the planet better so places like this can exist for future generations.

Happy Earth Day y'all!! If you haven't figured it out by now, I am super passionate about the environment and how I can create as small of a footprint as possible and yet still co-exist with the modern world. One of the reasons I went into health coaching is to help educate others about how our health and the health of the planet, is so intertwined. If you haven’t noticed, we are in the midst of a major health crisis world wide and much of it is due to the way we treat our environment. As those health issues continue to rise, you will also see a correlation with climate change and environmental issues, that environment in which we rely on for everything we need. Yeah, in case you missed that...we rely on the environment FOR EVERYTHING WE NEED!  With an emphasis on NEED too, because there is so much out there that we just want, but it serves no purpose for our survival. From the overuse of chemicals to cutting down rainforests to mono crops to CAFOs to the over-proccessing and packaging of our food and more, we are hurtling towards what could be a disaster in not only our health, but the health of the planet. It has been predicted we have 10 years left to change the way we live, before the effects of climate change are irreversible. Once that happens, we will see the effects of that climate become catastrophic on our health. We are so very connected with Mother Earth and we haven’t been treating her so well. So what can we do? The thought of having to make changes in just 10 years can be daunting. BUT, I believe we can do it!  One of the biggest changes you can make is around your food habits. That’s right, you heard me: CHANGE YOUR FOOD HABITS!!! Food is the one item we as humans ALL need and consume and it can cause so much detriment to our planet in the way it is grown, harvested, processed, & consumed. So, over the next 10 days I will be posting a tip per day to help you combat climate change by changing your food habits and the bonus is…these habits will also help you improve your health. So stay tuned, tag a friend or two so they can also follow along on said tips and at the end, I may just be having a little give-a-way😉
Happy Earth Day, today & EVERYDAY!
