Want to know what brewery to check out this weekend at @tapnyfest New York Craft Beer & Food Festival? Check out @communitybeer Beer Works. Established in Buffalo in 2012, they are committed to bettering the beer culture in Buffalo. They put a lot of emphasis on quality, sustainability, and community but it is not only part of their story, it's also in every beer you drink by CBW. Make sure you stop by and talk to their awesome crew and see just how they are helping shape a better beer culture.

It’s been tough for me to get photos edited and posted with working over the road this season being gone all week then at races on the weekends so it will take me a while to get pics posted from the other 3 MESC events. But here’s some photos from previous years at Lutsen. So sign up and come party with us one last time this year. Proud moment for all of us. Mateo and Felix (they’re ages 7 and 8) asked to ride the chairlift without me. I reluctantly disagreed up to the last minute, and decided to trust them. ✨Thank you Earth for your abundance;
Your beauty, your ability to sustain life and your giving soul.

I wish people would treat you better and take your life more seriously. I wish material possessions didn’t trump the longevity of you, our planet, I wish short term desire didn’t take precedent over you.

And while I can’t force people to make changes to their lifestyles, I promise to continue inspiring them the best I can over at @the.simple.planet, where everyday is Earth day.

Thank you, Earth, for giving us a home. I am forever grateful that my own personal connection journey lead me to also developing a strong relationship with you.

You da best 🧡 ✌🏼 Here are some of my fave pictures of me enjoying your gifts.

This Earth Day, remember to Think Before You Throw. You can help protect the environment and safely dispose of medications by taking them to a local drop box. 💊🛢 - No sharps allowed ❗️
.
.
Did you know that medications have been detected in lakes, rivers, reservoirs, and streams throughout the world? This could have serious impacts to human health and our aquatic friends.

Flushing drugs down the toilet sends them directly into our water supply and medicines thrown in the trash can get into the environment and/or be found by children or pets.

Pro Tip: If throwing away needles or other sharps, you can use a sharps container or an empty laundry detergent container for safe disposal! 💉

Happy Earth Day, everyone.  It's not only the big changes that make a difference, but also all the everyday little changes that add up. Celebrate Earth Day with us and take a moment today to actively find a way to reduce your waste. ⁣
⁣
-Keep an extra coffee cup in your vehicle for impulse coffee runs⁣
-Decline a straw at a restaurant (Our fav!) ⁣
-Turn off the water when you brush your teeth⁣
-Bring your own bags to go shopping⁣
⁣
Have more suggestions? We'd love to see them in the comments!⁣
⁣
*Photo was taken during a hike through Pine Mountain⁣. No filter. ⁣

Curracloe Beach in County Wexford is one of the most popular beaches in Ireland. Located 2KM away from Curracloe Village, this soft-sand beach is frequented by sunbathers and nature-lovers alike.

During the summer months, you’ll find that the area is bustling with life, as holidaymakers leave their home counties to take up residence in the holiday homes, campsites, hotels and B&Bs that surround the area. Later on, during the autumn and winter months, Curracloe Beach and its nearby forest become a hot spot for dog-walkers, joggers and anyone else in pursuit of a peaceful stroll.

The area itself is suitable for bathing, as it has a Blue Flag certification. This certification, which is awarded by the Foundation for Environmental Education (FEE), serves as a notice to beach-goers that the area and its surrounding waters have lived up to a number of strict regulatory standards.

Also, fun fact: Curracloe Strand, Ballinesker, were used for the filming of the D-Day sequence in Saving Private Ryan, due to similarity to Omaha, Normandy.
Curracloe Strand was also used for the Irish beach scene in the movie Brooklyn.

Starfish Sansevieria plants are rare but worth searching for!  Apart of the Sansevieria family they are wonderful air purifying plants. The plant has fan-shaped light green foliage with dark green circles from bottom to the top of the leaves. Although they are very forgiving, Sansevieria plants prefer indirect steady light with some direct sun. They can adapt to full sun conditions, and will also survive quite dim situations. Get FREE Monumental Expeditions stickers! How? Keep reading... It's important when outdoors and on the river to have plenty of drinking water. 
Here at Monumental Expeditions we often have guests that bring their own water in disposable water bottles. Unfortunately these bottles generally have a one time use, and most of the time we end up with a bunch of half drank bottles that guests leave behind. 
We would like to encourage everyone to bring their own reusable water bottle. We always have a large water jug with us in our vans that you can refill from prior to or after the trip.
Show up with a reusable bottle and we'll give you a FREE sticker for each one!

P.S. Here's a fun fact, if you look at an Arrowhead water bottle, especially from somewhere nearby, look at the label and see where the water came from. Most likely it will say it came from the Ruby Mountain spring, which literally flows into the Arkansas River. We float right by it on the Browns Canyon trip.

What happens when you use both products?

A: You get both younger-looking and well-rested eyes! Use Bright Eye Complex in the morning and Multi-Function Eye Cream at night to achieve maximum results.

I live and have my virtual and physical office/retreat space/and magical kitchen  in the The Cutest Snowbird Community in Paradise Valley.

It’s tucked away right in the middle of everything, and walking distance to everything you could dream of wanting/needing (Including My Sisters Closet 👠 👗 🥰) Sometimes things get deep in my intensive coaching sessions so we get outside to walk and move some energy. 
Sometimes we sit on the front patio with a view of @camelbackmountain. My friends and I do this too.

That’s pretty cool.

What’s also cool about this paradise place are my snowbird neighbors. 💞
I’m at the least, 20 years younger than all of them. They look out for me, they keep it real, they keep me in line, say nice things to my clients, and kindly offer high opinions of me and remind me to always laugh, take things lightly, but also expect the best. Part-time neighbors are great!

During snowbird season I started to visit them at #snowbird happy hour, at the pool, at least once a week. They know I don’t drink so they make sure I have water and snacks. 
Now, if they don’t see me for a few, Judy comes knocking at my door to formally invite me to their patio by the pool. It really is the little things. 🥰

It’s a great experience. My mom passed when I was 27 and my dad when I was 37. It’s nice to borrow parents and love on them.

Especially in this beautiful place!

So blessed! 💞🙏✨ #presentmoments #grateful #experiences

Johnnie Reid is immortalized in Stompin' Tom Connors' autobiography with at least a couple of mentions. But his legend also lives on among a generation of Canadian music icons who found a place to play (and eat!) and build their careers in a humble lounge across from the train station in Charlottetown. He maintained lifelong friendships with people like Anne Murray, Gene McLellan, John Allen Cameron and many others - he was even best man at Stompin' Tom's wedding to his wife Lena. ⁣
The presence of this piece from JR's in Voyageur stands as a testament to all of those club owners across Canada who take risks in supporting and incubating Canadian talent. The prominence of Canadian music on the world stage is rooted in places like JR's across the country.⁣
⁣
Find out more about the project and book a live presentation at https://www.sixstringnation.com⁣

Cake sugar. Basically a lump form of maple candy. This was one way Ziinzibakwaad was carried. Traditionally it was inside of a sugar cone (a cone made from a semi-circle of Birch bark that was then stitched up the one side and strung with a basswood cord), but this can be done at home using silicone muffin trays.

Blue sky day today in Glacier National Park!  GTTS is closed at Avalanche (6 miles up from LMcDL) Monday through Friday.  I am being told that it is open to approx. 3 miles past the loop (total of approx. 16 miles from LMcDL) after construction workers quit for the day (approx. 4.30-5.00pm) and of course, on weekends.  Camas Road is open to vehicles now, but is still a  great ride with lots of bikers out enjoying the views today!  Book an afternoon Going to the Sun Road on weekdays and get about 32 miles of amazing views! EARTH 🌍 DAY | Camp Cooking.
.
One thing we talked about first in planning this retreat was really teaching women that adventures off grid do not need to be wasteful. We have commited to having real camp dishware and teaching you how to cook, enjoy and clean up in a safe and wasteless way. .
.
While all of our meals will be catered, we are taking a portion of our Friday as a cooking off-grid class. You will create (with the help of our professional off-grid chefs) a gourmet meal you can easily recreate with your family and friends whole camping or just in our own backyard. .
.
We hope you do something that positively impacts the amazing earth we all share today and consider getting off-grid for a bit💚🌍🌱
.
